captions.text: [MUSIC - CHARITY VANCE, "ICING"]
-Hey, everyone.

I'm Mindy from Cute
Girls Hairstyles.

There's a photo that we saw
that has been recently released

of Prim from the new "Catching
Fire" movie, and her hair.
We thought it was so cool.

So today, I'm going to teach
you a tutorial that we're

calling the wrap-around Prim
braid that's of this picture.
It's really great.

So I've started by just
putting some curls in her hair.
You can see.
I just used a wand.

Really, really soft curls--
just add a little texture.
OK.

Now, we're going to start by
doing a deep left side part

and we're going to pick up
a little section of hair

right here and
start a lace braid.

Now, it's a Dutch
lace braid, which

means the stranding is
going to pop off her head.

And we're only going
to pick up strands

from one side, which is
what makes it a lace braid.

And I'm going to be picking
up from the side closest
to her part line.

So you can see I just
added some hair in there.

But on my left side,
I don't add hair in.

Now, we're just going to
work this lace braid straight

forward towards the front
of her face, at this point.

And when we get closer
to her forehead,

you can see I'm still only
adding in hair on one side--

when we get just a little bit
closer to her forehead I'm

going to begin to turn the braid
ever so slightly so that it's

going to make this nice, little,
rounded sweep-- that little arc
towards her forehead.
Let me turn her.

Now I'm going to continue the
lace braid till right here.

Now, at this point,
because you have

hair on this side and this
side you need to pick up,

I'm going to switch to
a regular Dutch braid.

So I'm going to go ahead
and start adding hair

in on both sides of
the braid right now.

And I'm going to just continue
this nice arcing pattern.

And it's going to just sweep
over the top of her ear.

You can see I'm just pulling
hair in-- both sides.

And the goal mostly
is just to make sure

that you have the hair
picked up right there.
OK.

And now that we have all of
the hair gathered to her ear--

let me turn her
again-- now I'm going
to switch back to at lace braid.

In the picture, you can see that
the braid goes on a 45 degree

angle from one ear to
the bottom of the other,
but there's hair left down.

So we don't want to
pick up all the hair

and put it into the
braid or we won't

have the hair we
need underneath.

So now I'm going to
only be adding hair
in on the top strand.
So I'm doing a lace braid again.

And now remember, we're trying
to work at a 45 degree angle.

So just keep that in the
back of your mind as you go.

And now you can begin to see
why those soft curls play in
as they hang down below.

Now remember, we're going to
the bottom of her opposite ear,

so I'm just trying to make
sure that my braid's headed
in the right direction.

And we want to make sure
we have all of this hair
into the braid.

So I'm going to make sure I
grab all this last bit right
here by her ear.

And make sure you pull this
little last piece pretty tight

so it lays really
snug against her head.

And now we're going to finish
it off with a regular braid.

And when you get to the end,
just secure it with an elastic.

Now, you can see that this
is very similar to a Katniss
braid.

And if you wanted to do a really
fun version of this braid,

pulling all of this hair
up and into the braid
would look great, as well.

So there's a second
option for you

if you don't want
to leave hair down.
Tuck that back.
And there you go.

You have the
wrap-around Prim braid.
I think this looks so pretty.
Let's spin her one more time.

You can see the beautiful arc
and then the little bit of a 45
all the way down to the end.
I think it's so cute.
Love it, love it.

Many of you guys
have been asking us

if our last two
children are adopted.
And they are, in fact, adopted.

Now, we have a story
that I have written up.

It was basically
my journal entries

from the experience
of adopting my son.

And I'll put a link
to it right here.
You can check it out.

It's a really touching
story that I loved.
I wrote it when he was born.

And we've had such a
positive response to it.

But if you're interested in
the story of how we got him,
you can check it out here.

And yes, I am writing
my daughter's, as well.
It's still in process.

So we hope you guys have
loved this hairstyle
and we will see you guys later.
-Bye.
[MUSIC - CHARITY VANCE, "ICING"]
-Look at sleepy.

It's pretty sad when
you're so tired you
fall asleep eating lunch.
And she's out.
[MUSIC - CHARITY VANCE, "ICING"]
